<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7390> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7390" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator? Asconius' remark (830 that C. Licinius Sacerdos (154), a candidate for the consulship of 63, was all but (tantum non) the first of his family to achieve a magistracy implies a previous senator of the name. See Wiseman, CQ 14, 1964, 123; NM 237, no. 225. Cf. Cic. Cluent. 134; Val. Max. 4.1.10, for an equestrian ancestor in 142.\n" .
